CRH, Deutsche Telekom, MVV Energie, National Grid: European Equity Preview

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   T a y l o r
-- 
2011-08-16T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/crh-deutsche-telekom-national-grid-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index rose 0.2 percent to 237.85. The
Stoxx 50 Index lost 0.1 percent to 2,245.75. The Euro Stoxx 50
Index, a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, increased
0.7 percent to 2,324.48.  CRH Plc (CRH)  : The Dublin-based building-materials maker
may report first-half earnings of 53.1 million euros, according
to the mean estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.
The shares rose 0.5 percent to 12.16 euros.  Deutsche Telekom AG (DTE)  : Europe’s largest telephone
company plans to start a venture with Vodafone Group Plc and
Telefonica SA this year to increase the use of mobile phones as
payment devices in  Germany , Handelsblatt reported, citing the
companies. Deutsche Telekom shares lost 0.1 percent to 9.52
euros.  MVV Energie AG (MVV1)  (MVV1 GY): The owner of German municipal
utilities said it will raise natural gas prices in October by
0.3 euro cents a kilowatt-hour, or about 5 percent, as the
company’s cost of buying the fuel gains. The stock surged 8.1
percent to 24.70 euros.  National Grid Plc (NG/)  : The manager of the U.K.’s power
network will limit flows through an electricity cable between
the U.K. and  France  until the middle of September. The shares
climbed 0.8 percent to 599 pence.  Solon SE (SOO1)  (SOO1 GY): The solar panel maker said it will
close a module plant in Tucson,  Arizona , to focus in  North
America  on developing solar projects for utilities and large
commercial clients. The shares rose 2.1 percent to 1.64 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
